CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 5, 1958, pg. A4, reads: "Thorofare Cashier-Checkers - For two weeks in month of February, the 59 stores of the Thorofare markets conducted a contest to determine the best cashier-checker of the year. In the left photo, Pauline Boyd, winner at the Centre Avenue store, is shown making change for a customer...  Although the voting was heavy at the Centre Avenue store, it was not sufficient to place a winner in the top five to compete in the finals. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Man, and women standing in grocery checkout line of cashier Pauline Boyd, in Thorofare Market, Centre Avenue
